    "explanation": "The structure described is CH3-CH2-C(=CH2)-CH3, which is 2-methylbut-1-ene. The longest carbon chain is 4 carbons (butene), with a methyl substituent on carbon 2, and the double bond between carbons 1 and 2. 2-methylbut-2-ene would have the double bond between carbons 2 and 3. Options A and C are identical; likely a typo in original. A is correct.",
