    "answer": 3,
    "exam": [
      "JAMB"
    ],
    "level": "easy",
    "topic": "Atomic Structure",
    "marks": 1,
    "explanation": "Electronegativity is the measure of the tendency of an atom to attract shared electrons towards itself in a chemical bond. An electronegative element has a high tendency to gain electrons (to form negative ions) or attract bonding electrons. Elements that lose electrons readily are electropositive.",
    "hint": "Electronegative = electron-loving.",
