    "exam": [
      "JAMB"
    ],
    "level": "easy",
    "topic": "Acids, Bases & Salts",
    "marks": 1,
    "explanation": "pH scale: <7 acidic, 7 neutral, >7 basic. X (pH 3) is acidic, Y (pH 5) is acidic, Z (pH 9) is basic. Lower pH means more acidic. X is more acidic than Y. Z is basic, not acidic, so it is the least acidic (zero acidity). Therefore, Z is the least acidic is correct.",
    "hint": "pH 7 is neutral; lower = more acidic; higher = more basic.",
