      "Carbon, iron and lead",
      "Carbon, iron and chromium",
      "Carbon, iron and copper",
      "Carbon, iron and silver",
      "Carbon and iron only"
    ],
    "answer": 1,
    "exam": [
      "JAMB"
    ],
    "level": "easy",
    "topic": "Organic Chemistry",
    "marks": 1,
    "explanation": "Stainless steel is an alloy primarily composed of iron with chromium (typically >10.5%) and carbon. Chromium provides corrosion resistance by forming a passive layer of chromium oxide on the surface. Nickel is also often added, but chromium is the key alloying element distinguishing stainless steel from other steels.",
    "hint": "The key element for rust resistance in stainless steel is chromium.",
    "timeLimit": 30,
