    "level": "medium",
    "topic": "Acids, Bases & Salts",
    "marks": 2,
    "explanation": "The student intended to prepare copper(II) nitrate, Cu(NO3)2, but reacted CuO with dilute H2SO4 (sulphuric acid). This would produce copper(II) sulphate, CuSO4, not copper(II) nitrate. To prepare Cu(NO3)2, CuO should be reacted with dilute HNO3 (nitric acid). This is the flaw.",
