    "explanation": "Cracking is the process of breaking down large, less volatile hydrocarbon molecules into smaller, more volatile molecules. This increases the yield of more valuable products such as petrol (gasoline), diesel, and other engine fuels. It does not primarily yield more lubricants, asphalt, or candle wax; those are heavier fractions.",
    "hint": "Cracking makes large hydrocarbons smaller, increasing fuel yield.",
    "timeLimit": 30,
