    "level": "hard",
    "topic": "Electrochemistry & Redox",
    "marks": 2,
    "explanation": "SO2 (sulphur dioxide) is a versatile gas. It acts as a reducing agent towards chlorine: SO2 + Cl2 + 2H2O → H2SO4 + 2HCl (SO2 oxidized to SO4²⁻). It acts as an oxidizing agent towards hydrogen sulphide: SO2 + 2H2S → 3S + 2H2O (SO2 reduced to S, H2S oxidized to S).",
    "hint": "SO2 can be both oxidized and reduced.",
    "timeLimit": 60,
