    "level": "easy",
    "topic": "Atomic Structure",
    "marks": 1,
    "explanation": "The mass of an atom is concentrated in its nucleus, which contains protons and neutrons. Electrons have negligible mass. Therefore, the atomic mass (mass number) is approximately the sum of the number of protons and neutrons. Ionization potential and electrochemical potential are properties related to energy, not mass.",
