    "explanation": "The rate of a heterogeneous reaction depends on the surface area of the solid reactant. Powdered zinc has a much larger surface area than pellets, allowing more frequent collisions between Zn atoms and H⁺ ions from the acid. This increases the rate of reaction. Greater volume of acid does not increase concentration; ice-bath decreases temperature and rate.",
